                        rajesh             Linux Training Labs
/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

System Requirements:

Virtual Machines or Physical Servers (Linux-based, Ubuntu/CentOS preferred)
Tools like VirtualBox, VMware, or cloud instances (AWS, GCP, etc.)

Lab 1: Introduction to Linux Basics

Basic Linux Commands: ls, cd, pwd, cp, mv, rm, touch, mkdir, rmdir
File Permissions: chmod, chown, chgrp
File Editing: nano, vim, vi
Process Management: ps, top, kill, htop
Package Management: apt-get (Ubuntu/Debian), yum (CentOS/RHEL)


Lab 2: User Management and Networking

User Management:
Create, modify, and delete users (useradd, usermod, userdel)
Managing groups (groupadd, groupdel, gpasswd)

File System and Disk Management:
Mount, unmount, and check disk usage (df, du)
Create and manage partitions (fdisk, parted, lsblk)

Networking Basics:
Check network status (ifconfig, ip, netstat)
Set static IP (/etc/network/interfaces or /etc/netplan/ depending on the distro)
Test connectivity (ping, traceroute, nslookup)

Lab 3: Working with Logs and System Monitoring
Log Management:
View logs (/var/log/syslog, /var/log/messages, journalctl)
Disk Usage and System Monitoring:
Disk space usage (df, du), process monitoring (top, ps)
Memory monitoring (free, vmstat)

Basic Troubleshooting:
Find system errors in logs
Use dmesg to view system boot messages

Lab 4: Package Management and Automation

Package Management (Advanced):
Installing, upgrading, and removing packages (apt, yum, rpm)
Install and configure repositories

Automation with Cron Jobs:
Scheduling tasks using cron (crontab -e, cron.d)
Check scheduled tasks (crontab -l)

